subtasks.details:
1. Create `sigma1-postgres-init-sql` ConfigMap in `databases` namespace containing a SQL script:
   ```sql
   -- Schemas
   CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS rms;
   CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS finance;
   CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS vetting;
   CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS social;
   -- public schema already exists
   CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS audit;
   CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS crm;

   -- Roles
   CREATE ROLE catalog_svc LOGIN;
   CREATE ROLE rms_svc LOGIN;
   CREATE ROLE finance_vetting_svc LOGIN;
   CREATE ROLE social_svc LOGIN;

   -- Ownership
   ALTER SCHEMA public OWNER TO catalog_svc;
   ALTER SCHEMA rms OWNER TO rms_svc;
   ALTER SCHEMA finance OWNER TO finance_vetting_svc;
   ALTER SCHEMA vetting OWNER TO finance_vetting_svc;
   ALTER SCHEMA social OWNER TO social_svc;

   -- Audit INSERT grants (no SELECT, UPDATE, DELETE)
   GRANT USAGE ON SCHEMA audit TO catalog_svc, rms_svc, finance_vetting_svc, social_svc;
   GRANT INSERT ON ALL TABLES IN SCHEMA audit TO catalog_svc, rms_svc, finance_vetting_svc, social_svc;
   ALTER DEFAULT PRIVILEGES IN SCHEMA audit GRANT INSERT ON TABLES TO catalog_svc, rms_svc, finance_vetting_svc, social_svc;

   -- Ensure no cross-schema SELECT: each role only has privileges on owned schemas
   ```
2. Set role passwords via Secrets (CNPG can auto-manage these or use `GRANT` statements).
3. Ensure the ConfigMap is referenced in the CNPG Cluster CR's `spec.bootstrap.initdb.postInitApplicationSQLRefs`.
